JOHANNESBURG England beat South Africa by two runs in the second One-Day International (ODI) in Southampton on Saturday.England set South Africa 331 to win, and restricted the visitors to 328/5 in their reply.With the win, England clinched the series at 2-0 up with just one game left to play.The third ODI will take place at Lords, in London, on Monday.Brief scores: England 330/6 v South Africa 328/5 (50/50 ov, target 331) England won by 2 runs.African News Agency